Here's a brief description of the infographic:

The infographic is a vertically structured, single-page visual created on Canva with a warm beige background. It is divided into four clearly defined sections:

What is Digital Literacy? — Features a laptop with a lightbulb icon and a short definition explaining digital literacy as the ability to use digital tools to find, share, and create information safely and effectively.

Useful Digital Tools for Students — Displayed in a green box with three icons representing calendar apps, note-taking, and communication tools.

Safe Internet Practices — Shown in a blue box with a shield/padlock icon listing three practices: using strong passwords, avoiding suspicious links, and keeping personal info private.

Professional Online Presence — In another green box with an illustration of a person at a laptop, explaining how a professional online presence helps make a great first impression for jobs and networking.

The design uses a clean, beginner-friendly layout with bold headings, simple icons, and a soft colour palette of beige, green, and blue, making it easy to read and visually appealing for students. Sonnet 4.6
